Trim and halve the @green beans{75%grams}(trimmed and halved).

Trim the @carrot{1}(trimmed and halved lengthways), then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces) into small pieces.

Zest then quarter the @lime{1}(zested and quartered). Roughly chop the @coriander{5%grams}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Halve the @chilli{1}(halved lengthways, core and seeds discarded) lengthways then discard the core and seeds. Finely chop.

Pour @water{300%ml}(cold and salted) into a #medium pot{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @rice{150%grams} and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pot from the heat.

Keep covered for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Add the @diced Irish chicken breast{260%grams} and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Fry until golden brown and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken. Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, remove from the pan and set aside.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to packaging we use to keep it fresh.

Return the pan to medium-high heat with another drizzle of @oil{to taste}, if necessary.

Once hot, fry the carrots and green beans for ~{1-2%minutes}.

Next add the onion, chilli and @garlic, ginger & lemongrass paste{1%sachet}.

Cook until the veg is tender, stirring often, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in lime zest, @soy sauce{2%sachets}, @red Thai style paste{1%sachet}, and @water{50%ml}.

Cook until sauce has reduced slightly, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the chicken and cook until warmed through, ~{1%minute}.

Season to taste with salt and pepper.

> TIP: Add a splash of water to loosen the sauce if necessary!

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and divide between plates.

Top with the spicy chicken stir-fry.

Finish with a squeeze of lime juice and a sprinkling of coriander.